## `<file-level: overview>`
<!-- checksum: rust-fsck-1 -->

### Purpose
Integrity checker. Runs `PRAGMA integrity_check` and a series of cross-table consistency checks, returning an `FsckReport`. Does NOT repair in v1 — reporting only.

Note: plan.v3 moved directory structure from `nodes.parent` to the `entries` table. All parent/cycle/nlink queries are therefore against `entries`, not `nodes`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use rusqlite::Connection;

use crate::errors::Result;
use crate::types::{FsckIssue, FsckKind, FsckReport, IntegrityResult};
```

---

## `pub fn run_fsck(conn: &Connection) -> Result<FsckReport>`
<!-- checksum: rust-fsck-2 -->

### Purpose
Entry point. Returns an `FsckReport` with the integrity-check result and any cross-table issues.

### Postconditions
- `integrity_check_result == IntegrityResult::Ok` iff `PRAGMA integrity_check` returns `"ok"`.
- `issues` lists every detected inconsistency. Empty on a clean DB.
- Issue kinds detected in v1:
  - `OrphanBlob`       — `blobs.inode` with no matching `nodes.inode`.
  - `OrphanXattr`      — `xattrs.inode` with no matching `nodes.inode`.
  - `OrphanSymlink`    — `symlinks.inode` with no matching `nodes.inode`, OR a `nodes` row with `kind='symlink'` but no `symlinks` row.
  - `DanglingParent`   — `entries.parent` or `entries.inode` references a missing `nodes.inode`.
  - `Cycle`            — reachable from itself via the `entries.parent` chain.
  - `NlinkMismatch`    — directory `nlink != 2 + count(child_dir_entries)`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn run_fsck(conn: &Connection) -> Result<FsckReport> {
    let integ: String = conn.query_row("PRAGMA integrity_check", [], |r| r.get(0))?;
    let integrity_check_result = if integ == "ok" {
        IntegrityResult::Ok
    } else {
        IntegrityResult::Corrupted
    };

    let mut issues = Vec::new();
    issues.extend(check_orphan_blobs(conn)?);
    issues.extend(check_orphan_xattrs(conn)?);
    issues.extend(check_orphan_symlinks(conn)?);
    issues.extend(check_dangling_entries(conn)?);
    issues.extend(check_cycles(conn)?);
    issues.extend(check_nlink(conn)?);

    Ok(FsckReport { integrity_check_result, issues })
}
```

### Failure Modes
- Returns `Err(Error::Sqlite)` on driver-level failure. A merely-dirty filesystem is reported via issues, not errored.

